Name: Decompensatory Shock
Treatments: Treat the Cause, Calm patient, Maintain normal temperature

Name: Compensatory Shock
Symptom Keywords: anxious, restless, disoriented, nausea, vomiting, dizziness
Treatments: Treat the Cause, Calm patient, Maintain normal temperature

Name: Myocardial Infarcation
Symptom Keywords: Lightheadedness, dizziness, anxiety, denial, radiating pain, persistent chest pain,
Treatments: Reduce anxiety and activity, Place patient in position of comfort, support patient with personal medications
Evac: Evac all patients with suspected cardiac chset pain, rapid evac any patient with a new onset of chest pain that is not clearly musculoskeletal

Name: Pnuemonia
Symptom Keywords: productive cough, wet lung sounds, malaise, fatigue, shortness of breath
